   {:e #blake3 "e8713b85af24d70267a8dc9ae6c50e3b93636be5060220aa3fba0b4c30e0f507" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "Session entity: :recon/trace-d24d452ab1cfb144; Session entity: :recon/trace-b3d57ad34f9ff8d9; Session entity: :recon/trace-648c11114b366c9f; Session entity: :task/t-5ab1b864; Session entity: :recon/trace-c53cd0043ca639db; Session entity: :task/t-bdb1738b; PHILOSOPHICAL-FRAMINGS: The Convergence Engine through psychology, linguistics, and philosophy of science. FREUD: id=LLM weights (raw associations), ego=agent reasoning (mediation), superego=braid (internalized standards, shapes what enters context window consciousness). JUNG: temperature schedule traverses archetypes — Fool (high T broad), Hero (medium T targeted), Shadow (H1 falsification), Wise Old Man (low T precise). Individuation = F(S) convergence. CHOMSKY: hypothesis generation is a generative grammar of inquiry — finite phrasing rules produce infinite valid hypotheses. CE-STEER's compile function IS the Merge operation. DELEUZE: knowledge graph is a rhizome (non-hierarchical, multiply-connected). Task graph is a tree (hierarchical DAG). The convergence engine operates at the boundary — compiling rhizomes into trees and back. High T = smooth space (Deleuzian deterritorialization). Low T = striated space (reterritorialization). LACAN: datom store IS the Symbolic Order. Observations are signifiers. Hypothesis launches signifying chain through LLM's unconscious (latent space). Free energy = gap between Symbolic and Real.; Session entity: :recon/trace-73c42bb9c5211fbf; ROUTING-RS COLLISION SAFETY: Five tasks modify routing.rs: CE-TEMP (generate_bridge_hypotheses), CE-OAR (compute_routing_from_store_inner), CE-META (PhrasingPattern + calibrate_phrasing_patterns), CE-STEER (compile_hypothesis_prompt), CE-TOPO (hypothesis type selection in routing). Collision analysis: CE-TEMP modifies generate_bridge_hypotheses (lines 1585+). CE-OAR modifies compute_routing_from_store_inner (lines 743+). CE-STEER adds a NEW function compile_hypothesis_prompt. CE-META adds a NEW enum PhrasingPattern + NEW function calibrate_phrasing_patterns. CE-TOPO adds hypothesis type selection WITHIN generate_bridge_hypotheses. SAFE PARALLELISM: CE-OAR and CE-TEMP touch DIFFERENT functions (routing vs bridge generation) — safe in parallel. CE-STEER and CE-META add NEW functions — safe with anything. CE-TOPO touches SAME function as CE-TEMP — must be serial (CE-TOPO -> CE-STEER dependency already enforces this). CONCLUSION: The dependency graph already serializes the unsafe pairs. No additional constraints needed.; KNOWLEDGE-WORK-TOPOLOGY-DUALITY: Task dependency graph and knowledge connection graph are DUAL structures governed by the SAME mathematics. Both are weighted graphs with spectral decomposition, Fiedler partition, CALM classification, Cheeger quality. topology.rs compiles task graphs into execution plans. The SAME machinery compiles knowledge graphs into exploration plans. Fiedler vector of the knowledge graph Laplacian points toward optimal exploration direction. This is the Fisher information direction — the natural gradient on the knowledge manifold. Multi-agent exploration is parallel geodesic computation on different charts, with CRDT merge combining charts into an atlas. Future CE-EXPLORE task would add braid explore plan --agents N using existing spectral machinery on the observation connection graph.; Session entity: :recon/trace-29b2c5a8e9abb6dc; CE-TEST EXPANSION: Four additional test areas required. TEST-16 CE-STEER: compile_hypothesis_prompt at T=0.1 (contains file path + spec ID), T=0.5 (contains shared keywords + relevant files), T=0.9 (broad open-ended, no file paths). Hole-type phrasing: beta0 produces 'How does X relate to Y?', beta1 produces 'X explains Y explains X — what EXTERNAL evidence?', beta2 produces 'boundary mapped, what is inside?'. TEST-17 CE-TOPO: 3 disconnected clusters -> beta0=3. Circular path A->B->C->A -> beta1>=1. Boundary observations -> beta2 proxy > 0. Euler characteristic chi = beta0-beta1+beta2. TEST-18 CE-MIND: 5 observations in same cluster with declining delta-F(S) -> Stuck. 5 observations across 5 topics no progress -> Lost. Contradictory observations -> Confused. High-progress deepening -> InFlow. Broad but shallow -> Skimming. Session start -> Normal. Mode transition logged as :runtime/cognitive-mode. TEST-19 CE-META: PhrasingPattern tracked per hypothesis. 5 FalsificationFramed hypotheses -> :meta/pattern-falsification-framed with count=5. Weights influence phrasing selection. CRDT merge combines pattern weights. Empty store has uniform weights.; CE-CONN TOKENIZATION: The approach references 'CRB tokenize_for_jaccard' which does not exist as a named function. The actual tokenization is in crates/braid-kernel/src/seed.rs (tokenize_for_search, private). For CE-CONN implementation: (1) Extract tokenization into a shared utility in crates/braid-kernel/src/lib.rs or a new crates/braid-kernel/src/text.rs module. (2) The tokenizer: lowercase, split on whitespace and punctuation, filter stopwords (the, a, an, is, are, was, were, this, that, it, of, in, to, for, on, at, by, with), filter tokens < 3 chars, deduplicate. (3) Jaccard: J(A,B) = |A intersect B| / |A union B|. Use BTreeSet<String> for determinism (C8). (4) This shared tokenizer is also used by CE-STEER (shared keyword extraction) and CE-META (pattern keyword matching)." :op :assert}
